com.lightysoft.logmx.business

Class LogURLParameter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.lightysoft.logmx.business.LogURLParameter

  • public class LogURLParameter
extends Object
    Defines a parameter that will be sent to a LogFileManager in order to locate the resource to open.
    A LogURLParameter defines a part of a LogURL.

    For example, a LogURLParameter could be a login: its name will be "login" and its value (set by the LogMX user via the GUI) could be "john".
    Since:
    LogMX v1.2.2
    Author:
    LightySoft
    See Also:
    LogURL, LogURLParameterType

      • LogURLParameter

        public LogURLParameter(String pName,
                       LogURLParameterType pType,
                       Object pDefaultValue,
                       boolean pOptional,
                       Object[] pPossibleValues)
        Construct an optional or mandatory LogURLParameter with its name, type, default value, and possible values
        Parameters:
        pName - Parameter name (e.g. "login")
        pType - Parameter type (e.g. LogURLParameterType.STRING)
        pDefaultValue - Parameter default value (e.g. "admin", System.getProperty("user.name"), or null if no default value)
        pOptional - Indicates whether this parameter is optional
        pPossibleValues - Possible values for this parameter (pType shall be LogURLParameterType.ENUM).
        The method toString() will be called on array elements to be displayed in LogMX GUI.
        Warning: Given array is cloned, but not its elements.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If pName or pType is null, or if pDefaultValue is not consistent with pType
        Since:
        LogMX v4.0.0
